text: Hugh Cholmondeley (14 May 1773 – 25 November 1815) was an English Anglican priest, most notably Dean of ChesterBritish History on-line from 1806 until his death.'Births, Deaths, Marriages and Obituaries' Liverpool Mercury(Liverpool, England), Friday, December 1, 1815; Issue 231 Cholmondeley was born in Cheshire and educated at Brasenose College, Oxford. ==References== Category:1770 births Category:19th-century English Anglican priests Category:Deans of Chester Category:Alumni of Brasenose College, Oxford Category:People from Cheshire Category:1815 deaths
